Nigerians, who had direct contact with the Italian diagnosed with Coronavirus in Lagos and Ogun states have been identified. This was disclosed by Lafarge Africa Plc on Friday. The Italian had visited the cement company after his entry into the country last Monday. SaharaReporters had exclusively reported that he was diagnosed of the disease in Ogun State before being rushed to Lagos where he was kept in Isolation. SaharaReporters had also reported that the Italian made contact with many people within and outside the cement factory and at the hospital where he was rushed to for initial treatment. 



